{"word":"Ζαχαρίας","slug":"Ζαχαρίας","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ζαχαρίας, ου, ὁ</el></b> [frequent name in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ OT\">OT</a>; ‘Yahweh remembers’] <b>Zacharias/Zechariah<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> priest and father of John the Baptist <b><a href='B:490 1:5'>Lk 1:5</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>; <b><a href='B:490 3:2'>3:2</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> a Z. who was murdered <b><a href='B:490 11:51'>Lk 11:51</a></b> and identified as son of Barachias (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Βαραχίας\">Βαραχίας</a></el>) in <b><a href='B:470 23:35'>Mt 23:35</a>; <a href='B:490 11:51'>Lk 11:51</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ζαφθάνι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ζάω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}